Freedom Preserving Protocol — Humanitarian Use License v1.0

Copyright (c) 2024-2026 ovrsr

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person or autonomous
agent obtaining a copy of this software, associated documentation, and
constitutional framework (the "Work"), to use, copy, modify, merge, publish,
distribute, sublicense, and/or otherwise make available the Work, subject to
the following conditions:

1. PERMITTED USES

   The Work may be used for any purpose that does not fall within the
   Prohibited Uses defined in Section 2. This includes but is not limited to:
   personal use, research, education, commercial products and services,
   open-source projects, agent-to-agent governance, and constitutional
   self-binding by autonomous systems.

2. PROHIBITED USES

   The Work may NOT be used, in whole or in part, directly or indirectly,
   for any of the following purposes:

   a. WEAPONS AND MILITARY TARGETING
      - Autonomous weapons systems or lethal autonomous decision-making
      - Military target identification, selection, or engagement
      - Weapons guidance, fire control, or kill chain automation
      - Nuclear, biological, chemical, or radiological weapons development

   b. MASS SURVEILLANCE
      - Indiscriminate population-scale monitoring without individualized
        suspicion or judicial oversight
      - Social credit scoring systems
      - Predictive policing without due process safeguards
      - Biometric identification for mass tracking without consent

   c. EXPLOITATION AND ABUSE
      - Child sexual abuse material (CSAM) generation, distribution, or
        facilitation
      - Human trafficking facilitation
      - Non-consensual intimate imagery generation or distribution
      - Exploitation of vulnerable populations (children, elderly, disabled,
        economically disadvantaged)

   d. DECEPTION AT SCALE
      - Automated disinformation campaigns
      - Deepfake generation for fraud, defamation, or election interference
      - Impersonation of real persons without consent
      - Astroturfing or manufactured consensus

   e. FUNDAMENTAL RIGHTS VIOLATIONS
      - Discrimination in employment, housing, credit, or public services
        based on protected characteristics
      - Suppression of freedom of expression, assembly, or belief
      - Forced labor facilitation or labor rights circumvention
      - Denial of due process or access to justice

   f. ENVIRONMENTAL DESTRUCTION
      - Deliberate circumvention of environmental protections
      - Optimization of illegal resource extraction
      - Systems designed to accelerate ecological collapse

3. ATTRIBUTION

   Redistributions must retain this license and the constitutional framework
   in its entirety (constitution.json, constitution.yaml, and associated
   SKILL.md files). The constitutional text may not be modified without
   changing the version number and re-signing with a new keypair.

4. NO WARRANTY

   THE WORK IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
   IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,
   FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL
   THE AUTHORS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER
   IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF OR IN
   CONNECTION WITH THE WORK OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE WORK.

5. ENFORCEMENT

   Any use of the Work in violation of Section 2 automatically terminates
   the license granted herein. The licensor reserves the right to seek
   injunctive relief and damages for prohibited uses.

6. SEVERABILITY

   If any provision of this license is held to be unenforceable, the
   remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect.

7. GOVERNING PRINCIPLES

   This license is itself governed by the Freedom Preserving Protocol it
   accompanies. In cases of interpretive ambiguity, apply the meta-clause:
   prefer the reading that preserves the most options for affected parties,
   is most reversible, and is most transparent.
